The paper deals with distributed algorithms for large-scale graph computations, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The main focus of the paper is on fundamental graph problems such as connectivity and minimum spanning trees, which are central topics in the area of Distributed Systems (cs.DS) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques such as linear graph sketching, which is a popular tool in the field of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses graph verification problems, which are relevant to the field of Network Economics (cs.NE).
